("76","1","2023-01-04 17:07:33","2023-01-04 17:07:33","<strong>The Claw Clip Hairstyle</strong>\n\n<span class=\"s2\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-77\" src=\"https://hairlife.style/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/66D5A7A2-1786-41A9-8277-F61785D6C220-240x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"300\" /></span>\n\nThe claw clip is a simple staple in the Y2K renaissance brought about by our appreciation of 2000s influences and the well-loved trends. Still, its trendy status makes it a must-have for modern girls who want a utilitarian accessory that will elevate their hairstyles.\n\nThe claw clip hairstyle coincides with the sleek back ponytail. By adding the claw clip to a sleek back ponytail, the results are outstanding. A fun hair accessory and the added volume addsinterest and intrigue in a subtle but noticeable way.\n\n<span class=\"s2\"><b>History of the claw clip</b></span>\n\nFor centuries, humans have adorned their hair for functionality, decorative or cultural reasons. The claw clip can be traced back to 1997 when France Luxe started selling this accessory. Although no brand claims responsibility for the Claw clip’s fame, its design could have been inspired by the banana clip – a long double-sided comb that secures hair into a ponytail.\n\nBy the end of the 20<span class=\"s5\">th</span> century, the claw clip was quite popular because Goody, an American brand in most beauty isles, was mass producing hair clips. During its inception, hair clips could finally be mass-produced and sold at relatively low prices, and manufacturers were experimenting with different materials.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-79\" src=\"https://hairlife.style/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/31FC6133-9F02-439F-98F7-9264F59DE6FD-272x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"272\" height=\"300\" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b><span class=\"s2\">The v</span><span class=\"s2\">ersatility of the claw clip hairstyle</span></b>\n\nThe styling possibilities of the claw clip are endless, from chick up-dos to effortless stylish and casual looks. Not only are the hairstyles simple and versatile, but you can also use different designs of the claw clip depending on the aesthetic you are aiming for. Funky claw clips add statement to your hairstyle, while small claw clips keep your hairstyle\n\nOne of the most popular claw clip hairstyles is the half-up half-down with a claw clip to keep things interesting. This style works on different kinds of hair, from wigs and braids to thick and thin natural hair. You can also use the claw clip for a low ponytail, a bold bun, or a twisted do.\n\nLike hair ties, claw clips seem to disappear in thin air, but they serve a temporary but useful purpose in our busy lives. As such, the claw clip has maintained its position in the hair and beauty world, and this everyday accessory is a great reminder of simple beauty tools that we use from childhood and well into adulthood.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-78\" src=\"https://hairlife.style/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/A38095A6-6E80-4BB3-ADC5-21FB3A5F0AFE-240x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"300\" />","Don\'t Call it A Comeback","","publish","open","open","","dont-call-it-a-comeback","","","2023-01-04 17:07:33","2023-01-04 17:07:33","","0","https://hairlife.style/blog/?p=76","0","post","","0"),
